<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 9:06AM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Weld
County through 945 AM MDT...
At 905 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of New Raymer, or 28 miles north of Fort Morgan,
moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Stoneham.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
